Extensive change of Chapter 6
6.1.1 revamped to be in accord with present circumstances; mention made
  of the changed circumstances associated to Schemas  and of the decision to
  pass to the use of <mchar> for MathMl character data, deprecating the use
  character entities.
6.1.2 similarly
6.1.3 similarly

  there is no need for duplicate short name forms; explanations revised
6.1.5 explanations revised and antiquated parts removed
6.1.6 special constant short forms &DD;, &dd;, &ee; and &ii;  removed;
  new Unicode codes inserted; three problem entities left in.
6.1.7 rephrased
6.1.8 rephrased; MMLALIAS and MMEXTRA blocks suppressed; a single chart
  for each ISO group with glyphs; 6.1.8.3 removed

revision 1.61
date: 2003-06-09 13:27:16 +0000;  author: jsdevitt;  state: Exp;  lines: +4162 -4084;
Various changes related to Andreas' long response on
Appendix C.  These include a number of new examples
illustrating points that were raised, validation grammar
and signature fixes.

- number of free variables in lambda

- elaboration on qualifiers as shorthand for domainofapplication

- additional example for domainofapplication

- clarification that fn is deprecated and alternative suggestion
for partially defined function.

- allowing degenerate case of no arguments for piecewise in which
case it is undefined.

- misc. signature fixes

- rewording of domainofapplication description

- new examples related to codomain and image

- minor grammar changes related to bvar counts, etc.
----------------------------

revision 1.46
date: 2002-12-15 21:46:09 +0000;  author: jsdevitt;  state: Exp;  lines: +17 -15;
Approved errata changes to the content mathml specification.  These include:

	- order of children in bvar should have been arbitrary.
		(content-markup.xml, about line 5199)

	- missing name space for an OpenMath reference in an example
		(content-markup.xml, about line 7096)

	- signature for root had children in wrong order , and there was no signature
		default case.  (about line 1806 in content-element-def.xml)

	- partialdiff signature was wrong.  degree should be after
		bvar, as described in section 4.3.2.2

	- syntax error in an example about p 1283 in content-element-def.xml
		(an extra closing tag for apply)

	(JSD)
----------------------------

revision 1.168
date: 2003-10-14 17:45:15 +0000;  author: jsdevitt;  state: Exp;  lines: +27 -27;
Given that the spec needs to be regenerated, I have fixed three items.
1.  &tau; was appearing as &pi; because there were two references to
    the same image.  I renamed the image for tau.  A new image is
    now generated.
2.  The first two examples of Section 4.2.5.1 (examples of condition) had
    logical errors. Both uses of "exists" with bvar and a condition
    require proper boolean arguments -- something that can evaluate to
    true or false.

Appendix C.  These include a number of new examples
illustrating points that were raised, validation grammar
and signature fixes.

revision 1.99
date: 2002-12-15 21:46:10 +0000;  author: jsdevitt;  state: Exp;  lines: +7 -3;
Approved errata changes to the content mathml specification.  These include:

	- order of children in bvar should have been arbitrary.
		(content-markup.xml, about line 5199)

	- missing name space for an OpenMath reference in an example
		(content-markup.xml, about line 7096)

	- signature for root had children in wrong order , and there was no signature
		default case.  (about line 1806 in content-element-def.xml)

	- partialdiff signature was wrong.  degree should be after
		bvar, as described in section 4.3.2.2

	- syntax error in an example about p 1283 in content-element-def.xml
		(an extra closing tag for apply)

	(JSD)

revision 1.49
date: 2000-03-27 20:52:29 +0000;  author: ion;  state: Exp;  lines: +3 -20;

Removed the resolved markers for issues

<issue id = "issue-ci-default-type">
<p>Shouldn&apos;t
<kw>ci</kw> have
<kw>none</kw> or
<quote>unspecified</quote> as the default type?</p></issue>

<issue id="issue-encoding">

<p>The various chapters use an interesting array of values for the
<kw>encoding</kw> attribute, namely <kw role="attval">Maple V</kw>, <kw
role="attval">Maple</kw>, <kw role="attval">MathML-Content</kw>, <kw
role="attval">MathML-Presentation</kw>, <kw role="attval">Mathematica
4.0</kw>, <kw role="attval">Mathematica</kw>, <kw
role="attval">OpenMath</kw>, <kw role="attval">TeX</kw>, <kw
role="attval">mathml</kw>. We need some normative text here about what
values this attribute can have, and we should have internal consistency
among the chapters at the very least. [I changed Maple V and Mathematica
4.0 to plain Maple and Mathematica.  It also appears someone has eliminated
the &quot;mathml&quot; value.  That leaves Maple, Mathematica, OpenMath,
TeX, and MathML-Presentation and MathML-Content.  --Robert ]</p></issue>
----------------------------

revision 1.33
date: 2000-10-31 03:33:18 +0000;  author: ion;  state: Exp;  lines: +8 -1;


Added paragraph to cover missing general attribute xref
<p>In order to facilitate compatibility with linking mechanisms,
all MathML elements accept <kw
role="attrib">xlink:href</kw> and <kw role="attrib">xref</kw>, and
for reasons of backward compatibility the strongly deprecated
<kw role="attrib">other</kw>.
</p>
----------------------------

revision 1.26
date: 2000-03-19 21:20:58 +0000;  author: rminer;  state: Exp;  lines: +160 -103;
Updated discussion of maction in chapter 3 to match chapter 7 changes about the other attribute.  Updated the references to include XPointer, XHTML 1.1, XHTML Modularization, and Building XHTML Modules.  Made all necessary corrections to chapter 7 from David's list.  The substanative ones were a change in the recommended namespace conventions for the <math> tag, MIME type is now text/x-mathml, XPointer is mentioned for linking into MathML, there is a new display attribute on the <math> tag to replace the deprecated mode attribute, and the other attribute is deprecated in favor of using attributes from other namespaces.

This is a major revision.  The main changes are changing a lot of future tense statements to present or past, reworking the text in acknowledgement that the top-level and interface elements for MathML are now in practice the same, redoing the linking in accordance with the new XLink draft, and revising the material about interactions with embedded renderers to reflect the current state of DOM implementation

revision 1.31
date: 2000-09-29 05:39:28 +0000;  author: ion;  state: Exp;  lines: +19 -35;


introduction.xml => contributors.xml
Removed Acknowledgments from Chapter 1 and put them in the
section now called WG Membership and Acknowledgments. (contributors.xml)
introduction.xml
Added bidi paragraph and target id under "Relation to Other Web Technology"
<p id="intro:bidi">The World Wide Web is a fully international and
collaborative movement.  Mathematics is a language used all
over the world.  The mathematical notation in science
and engineering is embedded in a matrix of local natural
languages.  The W3C strives to be a constructive force
in the spread of possibilities for communication throughout
the world.  Therefore MathML will encounter problems
of internationalization.  This version of MathML is
not knowingly incompatible with the needs of languages
which are written from left to right.  However the
default orientation of MathML 2 is left-to-right, and
it is clear that the needs for the writing of
mathematical formulas embedded in some natural languages
may not yet be met.  So-called bi-directional technology
is still in development, and better support for formulas
in that context must be a matter for future developers.
</p>
----------------------------

revision 1.169
date: 2007-12-08 07:40:54 +0000;  author: nsoiffer2;  state: Exp;  lines: +32 -42;
1.  I changed "dg" to "col" and then realized I didn't need "col" at all -- most examples used spacing="..." and those that didn't could.  So I have removed "dg" as a unit (and never added "col")

2.  I went with George's idea of using width, height, valign for the math tag and for mglyph.  We should discuss this further.  Having two different notions for how to specify baseline is not good.  I think we either need to depricate existing attribute names or break from common convention and make "height" mean "ascent"... Or convince ourselves that the two uses are really different and so can co-exist without conflict/confusion.

3.  I modified mcolumn's attributes as follows:
A) I changed "align" to be "justify" -- this specifies whether a row is left/right justified
B) I added "columnalign" with a spec that is the same as for mtable
C) I changed "baseline" to be "align" with a spec that is the same as for mtable.
----------------------------

revision 1.41
date: 2000-03-19 21:20:58 +0000;  author: rminer;  state: Exp;  lines: +9 -8;
Updated discussion of maction in chapter 3 to match chapter 7 changes about the other attribute.  Updated the references to include XPointer, XHTML 1.1, XHTML Modularization, and Building XHTML Modules.  Made all necessary corrections to chapter 7 from David's list.  The substanative ones were a change in the recommended namespace conventions for the <math> tag, MIME type is now text/x-mathml, XPointer is mentioned for linking into MathML, there is a new display attribute on the <math> tag to replace the deprecated mode attribute, and the other attribute is deprecated in favor of using attributes from other namespaces.

revision 1.12
date: 2000-03-19 21:20:59 +0000;  author: rminer;  state: Exp;  lines: +30 -2;
Updated discussion of maction in chapter 3 to match chapter 7 changes about the other attribute.  Updated the references to include XPointer, XHTML 1.1, XHTML Modularization, and Building XHTML Modules.  Made all necessary corrections to chapter 7 from David's list.  The substanative ones were a change in the recommended namespace conventions for the <math> tag, MIME type is now text/x-mathml, XPointer is mentioned for linking into MathML, there is a new display attribute on the <math> tag to replace the deprecated mode attribute, and the other attribute is deprecated in favor of using attributes from other namespaces.
----------------------------

revision 1.33
date: 2003-06-15 15:43:57 +0000;  author: jsdevitt;  state: Exp;  lines: +69 -41;
Fixes to grammar:

  1.  restored use of mmlarg as otherwise qualifiers can
      occur anywhere in any expression.

  2.  introduced non-terminal domainofapp to capture notion of
      a domainofapplication or a shorthand notation for such.

  3.  Modified apply rules to make use of domainofapp in a
	number of places where both were explicit, or where
	only conditions were allowed.

  4.  Fixed a piecwise to not make use of mmlall.
----------------------------

revision 1.31
date: 2003-06-09 13:27:16 +0000;  author: jsdevitt;  state: Exp;  lines: +4 -3;
Various changes related to Andreas' long response on
Appendix C.  These include a number of new examples
illustrating points that were raised, validation grammar
and signature fixes.

- number of free variables in lambda

- elaboration on qualifiers as shorthand for domainofapplication

- additional example for domainofapplication

- clarification that fn is deprecated and alternative suggestion
for partially defined function.

- allowing degenerate case of no arguments for piecewise in which
case it is undefined.

- misc. signature fixes

- rewording of domainofapplication description

- new examples related to codomain and image

- minor grammar changes related to bvar counts, etc.
----------------------------
